---
// ============================================
// PAGE — PRIVACY POLICY (ENGLISH)
// TEMPLATE: fill the highlighted fields and have it reviewed by a
// professional before publishing.
// ============================================
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const pageTitle = "Privacy policy";
const pageDescription =
  "How Atria Lab processes your personal data under the GDPR and Spanish data protection law.";
const actualizado = "July 2026";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <section class="pagina-hero">
    <span class="pagina-eyebrow">Legal</span>
    <h1 class="texto-degradado">Privacy policy</h1>
  </section>

  <p class="legal-nota">
    <strong>Template pending completion.</strong> Adapt the controller,
    purposes and retention periods to your real case. If you use forms,
    analytics or external tools, they must be reflected here. Have it
    reviewed by a professional before publishing.
  </p>

  <section class="legal">
    <p class="legal-fecha">Last updated: {actualizado}</p>

    <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Controller: <span class="dato">[Name or company name]</span></li>
      <li>Tax ID: <span class="dato">[NIF or ID number]</span></li>
      <li>Contact: <a href="mailto:theatrialab@gmail.com">theatrialab@gmail.com</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. What data we process and why</h2>
    <p>We process the data you provide voluntarily, mainly:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Contact details</strong> (name, email, phone and message)
        when you write to us or fill in a form, in order to handle your
        request and, where applicable, prepare a proposal.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Browsing data</strong> through cookies, as detailed in our{" "}
        <a href="/en/cookies">Cookie policy</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Legal basis</h2>
    <p>
      The basis is your <strong>consent</strong> when contacting us and our{" "}
      <strong>legitimate interest</strong> in responding to your request and
      managing the business relationship. For non-essential cookies, the
      basis is consent.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep your data for as long as the relationship lasts and, afterwards,
      for the legally required periods. When no longer needed, it is securely
      deleted.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Recipients</h2>
    <p>
      We do not share your data with third parties except where legally
      required. We may rely on technology providers (e.g. email, hosting or
      analytics) acting as data processors with appropriate safeguards:
      <span class="dato">[list the services you use here]</span>.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You can exercise your rights of access, rectification, erasure,
      objection, restriction and portability by writing to{" "}
      <a href="mailto:theatrialab@gmail.com">theatrialab@gmail.com</a>.
      You can also lodge a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency
      (<a href="https://www.aepd.es" target="_blank" rel="noopener">aepd.es</a>)
      if you believe we have not handled your request correctly.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
